Pressel2016
===========

Imagined Speech Database - Spanish vowels and commands.

Dataset Overview
----------------
  Code: Pressel2016
  Paradigm: imagery
  DOI: 10.1117/12.2255697
  Subjects: 15
  Sessions per subject: 1
  Events: vowel_a=1, vowel_e=2, vowel_i=3, vowel_o=4, vowel_u=5, arriba=6, abajo=7, adelante=8, atras=9, derecha=10, izquierda=11
  Trial interval: [0, 3] s
  File format: MAT
  Data preprocessed: True

Acquisition
-----------
  Sampling rate: 1024.0 Hz
  Number of channels: 6
  Channel types: eeg=6
  Channel names: F3, F4, C3, C4, P3, P4
  Montage: standard_1020
  Hardware: Grass 8-18-36 amplifier + DataTranslation DT9816 ADC
  Sensor type: EEG
  Line frequency: 50.0 Hz
  Online filters: {'highpass': 2.0, 'lowpass': 45.0}

Participants
------------
  Number of subjects: 15
  Health status: healthy
  Age: min=24, max=28
  Gender distribution: female=7, male=8
  Species: human

Experimental Protocol
---------------------
  Paradigm: imagery
  Number of classes: 11
  Class labels: vowel_a, vowel_e, vowel_i, vowel_o, vowel_u, arriba, abajo, adelante, atras, derecha, izquierda
  Trial duration: 4.0 s
  Study design: Cue-based imagined and pronounced speech of 5 Spanish vowels and 6 directional commands. Two modalities: imagined (silent) and pronounced (vocalized).
  Stimulus type: visual cue
  Stimulus modalities: visual
  Primary modality: visual
  Synchronicity: synchronous
  Mode: offline

